class.name: starchild.b4j.moony.code.osm.MapPane
class.event: TilesLoaded(Total as Int, Failed as Int)

method.name: Initialize
method.comment: Initialize the MapPane. The MapPane will have a size of 800x600 and display Mapnik STD tiles.

method.name: UseMapLiveDraggable
method.comment: Enable/Disable whether the Map can be dragged/moved with the mouse while showing live updates as it is being dragged.

method.name: RenderAllNow
method.comment:
Redraw all map tiles and all Map Markers, Polylines, Polygons, etc.
NB: Also Clears the SuspendRendering.

method.name: SetMapCacheFolder
method.comment:
Set a new drive/folder location where the Map Cache will be stored. NB: The new Map Cache folder will be created using the given map cache parent folder name in the path. ie. c:\Program Data\my-maps where: "my-maps" is the map cache parent folder.
By default the Map Cache is stored under this user's local data storage area. eg. c:/users/me/local/map-cache (for windows 7+)

method.name: SetAttributionOffset
method.comment: Move the attribution text up from the bottom edge of the map. Note: Need to do this if other controls/nodes are layed over the Attribution area. ATTRIBUTIONS should remain visible to the user at all times.

method.name: IsRenderingSuspended
method.comment: Returns: TRUE .. if map rendering is currently suspended.

method.name: SetTileExpiryInDays
method.comment: Set how many days the map tiles can be retained in the MapCache.

method.name: WorkOffline
method.comment: Set WorkOffline(True) .. to display only the Tiles already stored in the MapCache and don't attempt to fetch anymore from the internet. Note: WorkOffline defaults to FALSE.

method.name: ClearMapCache
method.comment: Delete all map tiles from the Map Cache for all OSM map sources.

method.name: Initialize3
method.comment: Initialize the MapPane. The MapPane will have a defined size and display tiles from TileSource1

method.name: Initialize2
method.comment: Initialize the MapPane. The MapPane will have a size of 800x600 and display tiles from TileSource1

method.name: SuspendRendering
method.comment: Temporarily suspend map rendering so you don't waste time when adding/deleting many markers, polygons etc.

method.name: ReduceMapServerLoading
method.comment:
A small delay can be inserted between every map tile request to help reduce overall map server loading.
Tile_Delay_in_Msec = 0 (no delay) ... library default = 50

method.name: UseSmartRendering
method.comment:
Enable a Smarter way of re-rendering the map and it's overlayed objects (MapMarkers, Polygons, Polylines and NodeHosts) ie. Makes map redraws and moving MapMarkers, MUCH faster.
Notes: Only re-renders the map tiles when it has to. ie. zooming and moving map. Re-render Overlayed objects ONLY when a SuspendRendering=False. You cann call the new function RenderAllNow() to force map tiles to be re-drawn.

method.name: IsCursorOverAnyMarker
method.comment:
Test IsCursorOverAnyMarker() at the start of a Map MousePressed event to decide whether to ignore this map event.
Note: A map's MousePressed event occurs first, before the Marker MousePressed event.
Returns TRUE .. if the cursor is currently hovering over any marker on the map.

method.name: ImportMapCache2
method.comment: Note: You should ClearMapCache to remove old contents first. Import map tiles for a specific OSM map source and merge them into the Map Cache.

method.name: ClearMapCache2
method.comment: Delete all map tiles for a specific OSM map source.

method.name: ImportMapCache
method.comment: Import all map tiles from an external storage location. and merge them into the Map Cache. Note: You should "ClearMapCache" to remove old contents first.

property.name: MapDraggable
property.comment: Enable/Disable whether the Map can be dragged/moved with the mouse.

class.name: starchild.b4j.moony.code.osm.render.ImageMapMarker
class.event: MouseClicked (Marker As MapMarker, Event As MouseEvent)
MousePressed (Marker As MapMarker, Event As MouseEvent)
MouseReleased (Marker As MapMarker, Event As MouseEvent)
MouseDragged (Marker As MapMarker, Event As MouseEvent)

method.name: SetScale
method.comment: Change the Size of the Marker on the map. ScaleFactor = 1.0 normal size (default value) eg. 0.5 = half size, 2=double size

method.name: GetPosition
method.comment: Get the current position of this Marker. NB: Similar to GetLat and GetLon but returns them as a Coordinate.

method.name: Initialize
method.comment: Simple Initialisation of a Marker using default map icons. ie. Dim IconIDs as DefaultMapIcons Displays in the nominated Size. eg. MyMarker.Initialize("MyMarker",IconIDs.PIN_RED,100,-31.123,115.123)

method.name: Initialize5
method.comment: Initialise a Marker from an existing Image object. Displays in the nominated Size. Also supports Rotation and Drop Shadow. eg. MyMarker.Initialize("MyMarker",MyIconImage,50,100,-31.123,115.123)

method.name: Initialize4
method.comment: Initialise a Marker from an existing Image object. Displays in the actual size of the image. Also supports Rotation and Drop Shadow. eg. MyMarker.Initialize("MyMarker",MyIconImage,100,-31.123,115.123)

method.name: Initialize3
method.comment: Initialise a Marker from an Image File. Displays in the nominated Size. Also supports Rotation and Drop Shadow. eg. MyMarker.Initialize("MyMarker",File.DirAssets,"my_icon.png",100,-31.123,115.123,0,10)

method.name: Initialize2
method.comment: Initialise a Marker using default map icons. ie. Dim IconIDs as DefaultMapIcons Displays in the nominated Size. Also supports Rotation and a Drop Shadow. eg. MyMarker.Initialize("MyMarker",IconIDs.PIN_RED,100,-31.123,115.123,0,10)
